WEBVTT

00:13.604 --> 00:15.488
<i>- I have concerns.</i>

00:15.566 --> 00:16.743
<i>- It's common for them
to watch pointlessly</i>

00:16.767 --> 00:18.300
<i>over their dead.</i>

00:18.376 --> 00:20.354
<i>- In terms of what is to be
done with him.</i>

00:20.378 --> 00:22.148
<i>The truth is, we don't know how</i>

00:22.172 --> 00:24.097
<i>the social body will react.</i>

00:24.174 --> 00:26.516
<i>If he can even be integrated.</i>

00:26.593 --> 00:29.695
<i>Their conditioning makes them
impulsive, erratic, dangerous.</i>

00:32.182 --> 00:33.690
<i>In the interest of stability,</i>

00:33.767 --> 00:36.735
<i>I would prefer
to handle this myself.</i>

00:36.812 --> 00:38.831
<i>- Counselor Marx is
an Alpha Plus, same as you.</i>

00:38.855 --> 00:41.364
<i>- No, that's my point,
not the same.</i>

00:41.441 --> 00:43.125
<i>- He's familiar to John.</i>

00:44.611 --> 00:47.120
<i>You see that?
What he's doing there?</i>

00:47.197 --> 00:49.122
<i>It's called prayer.</i>

00:49.199 --> 00:51.445
- I'm versed in their customs.

00:51.469 --> 00:53.835
I was Warden
of the Savage Lands for a time.

00:53.912 --> 00:56.171
- Not a custom.

00:56.248 --> 00:59.244
It's a communication.
That's their belief.

01:01.136 --> 01:02.761
- They also believe in fate.

01:02.838 --> 01:05.555
And witches.
And whales, so...

01:05.632 --> 01:08.558
- Whales are real.

01:08.635 --> 01:10.797
Were.

01:10.821 --> 01:14.523
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:14.599 --> 01:17.618
There was once a thing
called God.

01:20.522 --> 01:23.782
- In moments like this, John,
it's very hard to know...

01:23.859 --> 01:26.159
Which color soma to...

01:26.236 --> 01:28.328
Green, I think.

01:28.405 --> 01:31.507
No?
Well, maybe I'll just...

01:38.748 --> 01:40.507
I understand, John.

01:40.584 --> 01:41.978
You're burdened
by these feelings

01:42.002 --> 01:43.677
of parental attachment.

01:43.753 --> 01:46.065
And you know,
though it is a shameful thing

01:46.089 --> 01:50.016
to be a mother or a father...

01:50.093 --> 01:51.560
Well, it's intolerable,

01:51.636 --> 01:53.698
but no one blames you
for being an offspring.

01:53.722 --> 01:55.814
That is not your fault...
- Stop.

01:55.891 --> 01:58.191
- S... stop?
Stop what?

01:58.268 --> 01:59.620
- Stop talking.
- Why?

01:59.644 --> 02:02.329
- 'Cause I have nothing
to say to you.

02:04.274 --> 02:06.366
- Well, John, I'm...
- Don't.

02:06.443 --> 02:08.451
- You should know,
you belong here.

02:08.528 --> 02:11.997
After all, you did make it
through the Barrier.

02:12.073 --> 02:18.503
Which was... which was,
well, surprising, wasn't it?

02:18.580 --> 02:20.909
Don't worry.
It's my job to help you.

02:23.844 --> 02:26.595
No one is alone.

02:26.671 --> 02:33.527
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:58.086 --> 03:00.429
Don't you look nice?

03:03.017 --> 03:04.683
I sense you're still emotional.

03:04.760 --> 03:08.103
I have just the thing.
Um, this way.

03:28.700 --> 03:31.952
- You know,
I find your silence to be, um...

03:32.028 --> 03:34.371
It's intentional, isn't it?

03:40.870 --> 03:43.158
Is this your first time
in a lift?

03:43.182 --> 03:45.807
There is nothing
to be afraid of.

03:47.970 --> 03:50.845
- What exactly is the concern?

03:57.721 --> 03:59.198
You're strange.
On the rocket,

03:59.222 --> 04:00.825
you seemed more at ease,
when in fact,

04:00.849 --> 04:02.076
you were much higher then
than we are now.

04:02.100 --> 04:04.471
- No.

04:04.495 --> 04:05.871
- Something that might
interest you...

04:05.895 --> 04:07.790
This is New London's
largest building.

04:07.814 --> 04:09.476
Not the tallest, mind you...
- Stop.

04:09.500 --> 04:13.076
- But the, um, largest.

04:14.863 --> 04:16.382
Hmm.
That was fast.

04:22.329 --> 04:25.672
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:25.749 --> 04:28.745
<i>- Coming soon...
"Savage Lands 2."</i>

04:28.769 --> 04:32.554
<i>Bigger, better,
more savage than ever.</i>

04:32.630 --> 04:34.431
<i>And somewhere else.</i>

04:34.507 --> 04:36.152
<i>- I can't believe you got
the last tour</i>

04:36.176 --> 04:37.976
<i>of the original Savage Lands.</i>

04:38.053 --> 04:39.180
<i>I heard they put on a whole</i>

04:39.204 --> 04:40.757
<i>big, authentic riot
to celebrate.</i>

04:40.781 --> 04:42.897
<i>New London was
an absolute thrill</i>

04:42.974 --> 04:45.692
<i>while you were off doing
whatnot with Bernard Marx.</i>

04:45.769 --> 04:46.912
<i>There's
a new tropical simulation</i>

04:46.936 --> 04:48.912
<i>in the body district.
Amazing.</i>

04:48.989 --> 04:51.101
<i>It's as if you can feel
the water on your skin.</i>

04:51.125 --> 04:52.866
<i>I could take you.</i>

04:52.942 --> 04:54.337
<i>Of course, we could
actually go swimming,</i>

04:54.361 --> 04:56.130
<i>but what would
be the fun in that?</i>

04:56.154 --> 04:57.954
Still in bed?

05:00.509 --> 05:02.175
Hmm.
Mm-mm.

05:05.163 --> 05:06.883
There.

05:09.626 --> 05:12.580
So tell me.

05:12.604 --> 05:15.522
- It was amazing, wasn't it?

05:19.302 --> 05:21.061
What are you doing?

05:21.137 --> 05:22.365
- What do you think I'm doing?

05:22.389 --> 05:23.925
I know when you want
a little tickle.

05:23.949 --> 05:26.450
- Oh, not now.

05:32.374 --> 05:34.934
You've always had
the prettiest ears.

05:34.984 --> 05:36.752
- Not now.

05:38.488 --> 05:41.915
- What's up with you?

05:41.991 --> 05:43.925
- I don't know.

05:47.163 --> 05:49.475
- After all that Savage fun,
it's back to the real world.

05:49.499 --> 05:51.536
You missed me, didn't you?

05:53.503 --> 05:55.114
<i>- Hello there.</i>

05:55.138 --> 05:59.099
My name's Anna, and I want
to welcome you to New London.

05:59.175 --> 06:01.559
In fact, we all do!

06:01.636 --> 06:03.561
We're here to help
you transition

06:03.638 --> 06:07.510
from your primitive world
of hardship and strife to ours,

06:07.534 --> 06:11.277
an evolved society
of harmony and happiness.

06:11.354 --> 06:14.656
<i>To experience all the wonders
New London has to offer,</i>

06:14.732 --> 06:17.002
<i>you'll need to be fitted
with an optic interface.</i>

06:17.026 --> 06:21.413
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:21.489 --> 06:23.507
<i>In addition
to operating numerous</i>

06:23.583 --> 06:25.959
<i>environmental controls
and entertainments,</i>

06:26.035 --> 06:28.907
<i>your optic interface
connects you to Indra,</i>

06:28.931 --> 06:32.924
<i>and Indra connects you
to, well, everyone.</i>

06:33.001 --> 06:36.302
<i>With your OI,
you'll always be connected.</i>

06:36.379 --> 06:38.847
You can see
through anyone's eyes

06:38.923 --> 06:40.682
and they can look through yours

06:40.758 --> 06:43.935
and see just how fabulous
your life is.

06:45.280 --> 06:47.241
Your OI lets everyone know
who you are...

06:48.558 --> 06:50.692
<i>and who they are to you.</i>

06:50.768 --> 06:52.777
There's a place
for you here, John.

06:52.854 --> 06:54.988
<i>All: We can't wait
to meet you!</i>

06:55.064 --> 06:58.658
- Oh, this is the one, huh?
- This is John.

06:58.735 --> 07:01.578
John, this Beta
is... both: Julian.

07:01.654 --> 07:04.673
- Nice to meet you, John.
Welcome to New London.

07:06.659 --> 07:09.239
- He's not speaking.
- He doesn't speak?

07:09.263 --> 07:12.464
- No, he does,
he just... he's not.

07:12.540 --> 07:14.727
- I hear some of them
are defective.

07:14.751 --> 07:17.427
- No, he's not defective,
he's just, uh...

07:17.504 --> 07:19.565
John's perfectly normal.
Aren't you, John?

07:19.589 --> 07:21.431
- Are you sure this is safe?

07:21.508 --> 07:24.350
- Yes, it's safe.
Why don't... do your job.

07:24.427 --> 07:26.111
- Sure.

07:29.283 --> 07:31.243
- It's all right.
You'll thank me.

07:31.276 --> 07:33.579
- You just keep your eyes
on the projection there.

07:33.603 --> 07:35.849
He can hear me, right?

07:35.873 --> 07:38.334
So, how'd you get
stuck with this?

07:38.358 --> 07:41.117
- I was chosen.
- Yikes.

07:41.194 --> 07:42.702
- It's a special assignment.

07:42.779 --> 07:45.788
I'm charged
with John's care until...

07:45.865 --> 07:47.718
Well, until he becomes part
of the social body, I suppose.

07:47.742 --> 07:49.834
- Fun.
- What?

07:49.911 --> 07:51.252
- Look this way.

07:52.589 --> 07:55.215
I'm just, uh,
getting some measurements.

07:55.291 --> 07:57.287
- He... he's just getting
some measurements, John.

07:57.311 --> 07:59.010
- DS392.

07:59.087 --> 08:00.782
We have this profile
in the system.

08:00.806 --> 08:02.441
- We don't. He was conceived
in the Savage way.

08:02.465 --> 08:05.099
We'll have
to customize something.

08:08.772 --> 08:12.051
- His ocular dimensions,
the, uh, bio-topical details

08:12.075 --> 08:14.620
of his target neurons...
They're rare.

08:14.644 --> 08:18.371
Alpha.
Alpha-Exotic, even.

08:18.448 --> 08:20.668
Less than 1%,
but he's definitely...

08:20.692 --> 08:24.586
- He's not an Alpha.
- Well, his eyeball is.

08:28.717 --> 08:30.461
- He's coming back.
He's coming right back

08:30.485 --> 08:34.513
with just the thing to get your
levels up where they belong.

08:39.377 --> 08:41.010
You're choosing to be angry.

08:41.087 --> 08:42.532
You can't help
your conditioning, John.

08:42.556 --> 08:44.013
None of us can.

08:44.090 --> 08:48.434
But eventually, you'll learn
to think like we do

08:48.511 --> 08:52.272
about these sorts of things.
Endings.

08:52.348 --> 08:54.190
And I'll help you.

08:54.267 --> 08:56.568
You don't need to be unhappy.

09:01.357 --> 09:03.836
- You don't wanna talk to me?
Fine, fine.

09:03.860 --> 09:05.671
Well, you're gonna have
to talk to someone, John.

09:05.695 --> 09:08.588
This is where you are.
There is nowhere else.

09:11.618 --> 09:13.459
H-Henry!

09:13.536 --> 09:14.977
- Uh, where are you going?

09:15.054 --> 09:16.974
- Uh, just give me one minute.
I'll be right back.

09:16.998 --> 09:19.007
Henry!

09:19.083 --> 09:22.135
- There's no need to worry.
The OI does all the work.

09:23.880 --> 09:26.639
Nothing is ever going to look
the same again.

09:28.518 --> 09:29.762
- Fuck off!

09:29.786 --> 09:31.530
- Well, you spoke,
that... that's good.

09:45.902 --> 09:48.161
There he is!

09:48.237 --> 09:51.039
- What's his level?

10:01.275 --> 10:03.379
- Now, it's a fascinatingly
complex machine,

10:03.403 --> 10:05.206
the... the autocar.
It's quite a challenge.

10:05.230 --> 10:08.890
Um, but somehow I found
myself up to the task.

10:08.966 --> 10:10.402
Wow.

10:10.426 --> 10:14.562
- A task that somehow
even a Savage can master?

10:15.890 --> 10:17.907
- Well, sure, but...

10:20.436 --> 10:22.111
What?

10:37.245 --> 10:39.741
<i>- Who is he?
- What is he?</i>

10:39.765 --> 10:41.743
<i>- Is he real?
- Who is he?</i>

10:41.767 --> 10:44.245
<i>I don't know.</i>

10:44.269 --> 10:46.456
<i>- I don't know.
- He's a Savage?</i>

10:50.942 --> 10:53.768
<i>- A Savage.
- It's a Savage.</i>

11:05.198 --> 11:07.268
- Maintain contact
with your Alpha.

11:11.446 --> 11:14.881
- Takes you back, doesn't it?
- Mm.

11:16.951 --> 11:19.781
- I remember
my first correction.

11:19.805 --> 11:22.839
Smell of the singed little
hairs on my arm.

11:22.915 --> 11:26.634
Once was enough for me.

11:28.463 --> 11:32.565
But not for you.
I used to think you enjoyed it.

11:32.642 --> 11:35.852
And then I realized
you couldn't help it.

11:35.928 --> 11:39.425
It's just how you are.

11:39.449 --> 11:41.190
- How am I?

11:41.267 --> 11:44.444
- You know, you still get that
look in your eye sometimes,

11:44.520 --> 11:46.307
like when we were little.

11:46.331 --> 11:50.311
You'd go somewhere else
in your head, and then... zap!

11:50.335 --> 11:51.909
Ow!

11:54.030 --> 11:55.299
- Frannie, I'm sorry, I didn't...

11:55.323 --> 11:58.842
- No, it's nothing.
Nothing happened.

12:05.341 --> 12:07.328
So I'll see you tonight
at the Feelie?

14:12.853 --> 14:14.602
- You know what
I like about you, Marx?

14:14.679 --> 14:16.340
- I'm very disappointed.

14:16.364 --> 14:18.025
I left him with a seemingly
capable Beta, and I...

14:18.049 --> 14:20.141
- You always meet
my expectations.

14:20.217 --> 14:21.812
- But not to worry,
we can track him.

14:21.836 --> 14:23.488
He's sure to create emotional
disturbances wherever he goes.

14:23.512 --> 14:25.313
- When I sent you
to the Savage Lands,

14:25.389 --> 14:27.899
I thought you'd find your place.

14:27.975 --> 14:31.494
That maybe, for once
in your life, you could fit.

14:31.571 --> 14:34.155
I wanted that for you, Bernard.

14:34.231 --> 14:36.490
But you never quite
follow through, do you?

14:36.567 --> 14:37.847
- Sir, I...

14:37.902 --> 14:39.182
- You know,
I had a thought once.

14:39.236 --> 14:40.505
If I threw you off
the precipice,

14:40.529 --> 14:43.581
somehow you'd find
a way to not hit the water.

14:43.658 --> 14:44.999
- It's a matter of time, sir.

14:45.076 --> 14:46.428
I know John,
I know how he thinks.

14:46.452 --> 14:48.928
- You should never
have come back.

14:50.915 --> 14:54.842
- Well, I did come back, sir.
So it seems you made a mistake.

14:54.919 --> 14:57.665
- There are no mistakes.

14:57.689 --> 15:00.973
Well, perhaps one.

15:01.050 --> 15:04.027
Now you listen
to...

18:04.191 --> 18:06.334
- You're lost.

18:08.863 --> 18:10.797
- My mother's dead.

18:36.741 --> 18:38.858
Who are you?

18:38.934 --> 18:40.985
- I'm here to help.

18:41.061 --> 18:43.871
- You all say that.

18:43.948 --> 18:46.824
- I'm different.

18:46.901 --> 18:49.105
I'm important.

18:49.129 --> 18:51.212
I'm not like the others.

18:51.289 --> 18:53.956
I can give you what you want.

18:54.033 --> 18:55.541
- You don't know what I want.

18:55.618 --> 18:59.795
- Of course I do.
We want the same thing.

18:59.872 --> 19:02.047
A way out.

19:02.124 --> 19:04.133
Yes?

19:06.837 --> 19:08.929
I was there when they
brought you in,

19:09.006 --> 19:10.631
screaming for your mother.

19:10.708 --> 19:16.437
The word means nothing to them.
Her death means nothing.

19:16.513 --> 19:19.440
What they've done to you
is unconscionable.

19:19.516 --> 19:21.734
What they will do,
you can't imagine.

19:25.231 --> 19:27.656
If you come with me now,
you have a chance.

19:27.733 --> 19:30.910
- Come where?

19:30.986 --> 19:34.338
- John, there isn't much time.

19:35.866 --> 19:38.301
You don't belong here.

19:50.839 --> 19:53.024
- What are you doing?
- N-nothing.

19:53.100 --> 19:55.059
Hi, how are you?

19:55.135 --> 19:56.463
- Is this a bad time?

19:56.487 --> 19:57.906
- Uh, no, no.
I didn't...

19:57.930 --> 19:59.291
Sorry, I didn't...
Didn't think you were due

19:59.315 --> 20:00.467
for another session until, um...

20:00.491 --> 20:01.908
- Oh, no, I'm... I'm not.

20:01.984 --> 20:05.986
I guess I thought
I'd come up here to talk.

20:08.032 --> 20:11.116
- Oh.
Um, of course.

20:11.193 --> 20:12.752
Please.

20:14.446 --> 20:17.840
What should we, uh...
What should we talk about?

20:20.953 --> 20:23.012
- I haven't been myself.

20:23.089 --> 20:25.600
Who have you been?

20:25.624 --> 20:26.993
- It was different there,
wasn't it?

20:27.017 --> 20:28.144
- It's best not to think
about it.

20:28.168 --> 20:29.404
- Well, all I do
is think about it.

20:29.428 --> 20:30.563
- Oh, then you've come
to the right place.

20:30.587 --> 20:32.596
How are your levels?

20:32.673 --> 20:34.899
- I want to think about it.

20:38.095 --> 20:39.748
It's like...

20:39.772 --> 20:41.647
It's like a piece of me
got stuck there,

20:41.724 --> 20:43.761
or a piece of it
got stuck in me...

20:43.785 --> 20:46.694
Um, I... I don't know.

20:46.770 --> 20:48.248
Do you ever wonder
what would've happened

20:48.272 --> 20:50.289
if we'd never left
that hotel room?

20:51.734 --> 20:53.784
- Yes.

20:53.861 --> 20:54.946
- And we'd probably all
have done

20:54.970 --> 20:57.713
like every Alpha and Beta,
just...

20:57.790 --> 20:59.290
gone on a tour.

20:59.366 --> 21:02.626
Orgy in the pool.
Come back here.

21:02.703 --> 21:04.169
And nothing would be different.

21:04.246 --> 21:06.005
Soma, work,
Pleasure Garden, Feelie.

21:06.081 --> 21:09.258
- It can still be like that,
Lenina, it's...

21:09.335 --> 21:11.302
Nothing has changed.

21:11.378 --> 21:13.479
- I did.

21:16.842 --> 21:19.810
- Nonsense.
I'm gonna get you a yellow.

21:19.887 --> 21:21.957
- I'm trying to talk to you.
I'm trying to tell... tell you...

21:21.981 --> 21:23.564
- No, I'm listening.

21:23.640 --> 21:25.160
It's just you're
not making much sense.

21:25.184 --> 21:26.609
- I was born a Beta Plus.

21:26.685 --> 21:27.829
I'll be a Beta Plus
when the soma man comes.

21:27.853 --> 21:29.278
I really don't choose anything.

21:29.355 --> 21:30.529
- It's chosen for you.

21:30.606 --> 21:32.072
That's the beauty of the system.

21:32.149 --> 21:33.501
- Don't do that.
Don't be an Alpha right now.

21:33.525 --> 21:36.002
Just be Bernard.

21:37.529 --> 21:38.798
- Now, I don't know
what you mean

21:38.822 --> 21:39.966
when you say things like that.
- You do.

21:39.990 --> 21:41.343
I know you do.
When we were there...

21:41.367 --> 21:44.293
- We're not there.
We're here.

21:44.370 --> 21:49.056
And we are lucky to be alive,
Lenina, so...

21:54.671 --> 21:58.432
- Where is he?
How is he?

21:58.509 --> 21:59.859
Who?

21:59.935 --> 22:02.172
- Bernard.
- He... don't worry about him.

22:02.196 --> 22:03.698
- His mother died.
- And?

22:03.722 --> 22:07.450
- Well, that matters...
to them.

22:07.526 --> 22:09.496
- He's fine.
- I want to talk to him.

22:09.520 --> 22:12.780
- I don't think that's
a good idea for either of you.

22:12.856 --> 22:14.856
- I think I liked you
better there.

22:16.902 --> 22:18.410
- You're right.

22:18.487 --> 22:19.981
We never should've left
the hotel room.

22:20.005 --> 22:21.492
I should never have let you
talk me into it.

22:21.516 --> 22:23.957
- We both wanted...
- W-why did you come here?

22:24.034 --> 22:25.520
- Bernard!
- W-what do you want me to say?

22:25.544 --> 22:27.127
D-do you want me
to validate this?

22:27.204 --> 22:30.339
Your... your solipsism, your...
Here's my recommendation.

22:30.416 --> 22:32.727
If you wanna go back to feeling
like yourself, act like it.

22:32.751 --> 22:34.729
Take your soma, go to work,
go to the Pleasure Gardens,

22:34.753 --> 22:36.247
do your duty,
do all the things you did

22:36.271 --> 22:38.647
before we went to that
horrible place, because...

22:40.759 --> 22:42.610
Because you were happy.

22:44.680 --> 22:46.717
- I wasn't.
And neither were you.

22:46.741 --> 22:49.525
- Everybody's happy,
unless they choose not to be.

23:01.080 --> 23:02.846
<i>You think I'm weak.</i>

23:02.923 --> 23:04.384
You think there's some part
of me that's missing,

23:04.408 --> 23:06.041
you and everyone else.

23:06.118 --> 23:08.585
Well, you're right.
We're not equal.

23:08.662 --> 23:11.013
Because I've had to make
myself something more.

23:11.090 --> 23:13.966
I was shot, burned, hunted.

23:14.042 --> 23:16.218
You have no idea what I've lost.

23:16.295 --> 23:20.876
And yet, I'm... And
yet, I'm still here.

23:20.900 --> 23:22.152
What other Alpha Plus
has ever given

23:22.176 --> 23:23.754
more of himself
for the social body?

23:23.778 --> 23:25.405
And that's who
you try to banish?

23:25.429 --> 23:26.937
It can't be done.

23:27.014 --> 23:28.634
So you see,
the mistake was not mine, sir.

23:28.658 --> 23:31.200
It was yours.

23:31.277 --> 23:32.604
You think I'm weak.

23:32.628 --> 23:34.056
You think there's some
part of me that's...

23:56.084 --> 23:58.853
Who's being private now?

24:24.863 --> 24:26.088
- Try not to draw attention.

24:30.970 --> 24:33.031
- I don't like the way
they look at me.

24:33.055 --> 24:36.548
- You're a Savage, a curiosity.

24:36.625 --> 24:41.345
If I let them, they'll put you
in a little box on display,

24:41.421 --> 24:44.773
feed you pills until
you can't remember who you are.

24:46.486 --> 24:48.589
Don't worry,
we're going somewhere safe.

24:48.613 --> 24:50.312
Somewhere beautiful.

24:50.389 --> 24:52.114
- I just want
to get out of here.

24:58.313 --> 25:01.949
- What you see is an ocean.

25:12.127 --> 25:14.512
- Holy shit.

25:15.381 --> 25:18.006
- Here it comes.

25:18.083 --> 25:21.552
That flivver will take you
to the last rocket.

25:21.628 --> 25:25.764
- To where?
- To your home.

25:25.841 --> 25:28.350
You wouldn't believe what
I had to do to arrange it.

25:30.762 --> 25:32.863
There won't be another.

25:43.317 --> 25:45.042
Get in.

25:46.278 --> 25:48.203
Get in.

25:48.280 --> 25:50.275
- I can't go back.

25:50.299 --> 25:51.873
- There's no life for you here.

25:51.950 --> 25:55.197
- I go back, they'll kill me.
- Not to your old life.

25:55.221 --> 25:58.213
You can be something new.

25:58.290 --> 26:01.550
There is more beyond the
Barrier than you can imagine.

26:01.627 --> 26:06.638
Wide open spaces.
Roads leading...

26:06.715 --> 26:09.358
I don't know where they go,
but they're beautiful.

26:09.435 --> 26:12.319
There are people out there.

26:12.396 --> 26:13.895
- How do you know that?

26:13.972 --> 26:17.274
- All Alphas go there...
when we're young.

26:18.477 --> 26:20.110
- Don't lie to me.

26:24.584 --> 26:27.167
You were Warden
of the Savage Lands?

26:28.987 --> 26:31.913
- It doesn't matter now.
- It mattered to her,

26:31.990 --> 26:34.916
to my mom.
You remember Linda.

26:34.993 --> 26:37.322
- Get in.
- She'd get drunk every night

26:37.346 --> 26:39.921
trying to bring you back.

26:39.998 --> 26:44.176
She waited for you for years,
decades.

26:44.252 --> 26:46.331
- Get in.

26:46.355 --> 26:47.846
- Get off of me!

26:50.676 --> 26:55.103
What happened?

26:55.180 --> 26:57.773
She always said you were
coming back for us.

26:57.849 --> 27:00.942
You never even tried, did you?

27:01.019 --> 27:03.445
Did you?

27:03.522 --> 27:06.490
- I wanted her.

27:06.566 --> 27:09.376
And she wanted me.

27:10.737 --> 27:15.916
We were monogamous,
and...

27:15.992 --> 27:18.960
Then she started to swell.

27:19.037 --> 27:20.556
We didn't know
what was happening.

27:20.580 --> 27:21.672
How could we know?

27:21.748 --> 27:23.882
- She loved you.

27:23.959 --> 27:27.636
- I know.
That's why she wanted me to go.

27:27.713 --> 27:28.887
- Bullshit.

27:28.964 --> 27:30.441
- There was no way
for her to come back.

27:30.465 --> 27:32.794
She wouldn't leave you.

27:32.818 --> 27:36.228
There are no mothers here.

27:36.304 --> 27:39.147
No fathers, no sons.

27:39.224 --> 27:42.284
There is now.

27:46.440 --> 27:47.906
- There can't be.

27:55.374 --> 27:57.165
John, wait!

27:57.242 --> 28:03.305
♪ ♪

29:04.643 --> 29:06.746
He just keeps going on and on

29:06.770 --> 29:10.113
and on, and he doesn't know
when to stop, and...

29:10.190 --> 29:13.200
Oh, Marx.
- We have a problem.

29:13.276 --> 29:15.452
- Uh-huh.

29:15.529 --> 29:17.609
I guess we'll have
to pick this up later.

29:21.701 --> 29:24.503
See you later.

29:30.210 --> 29:31.521
- In the Savage way
of conception,

29:31.545 --> 29:33.386
certain characteristics
are passed down...

29:33.463 --> 29:35.016
- Whoa, Bernard, hold on.
Slow down.

29:35.040 --> 29:36.317
- Inherited from one
of two genetic contributors...

29:36.341 --> 29:39.059
- Bernard!
- What?

29:39.135 --> 29:41.311
- How are your levels?
- My levels?

29:41.388 --> 29:44.022
No, look.
They're identical.

29:44.099 --> 29:47.943
This is the Director's,
and this is the Savage's.

29:48.019 --> 29:49.956
- What are you doing
with the Director's optic?

29:49.980 --> 29:52.289
- He left it on his desk,
in his office.

29:52.366 --> 29:54.377
- And what were you doing
in his office?

29:54.401 --> 29:56.910
- You're missing the point.
- Bernard.

29:56.987 --> 30:00.339
Sit down, please.

30:06.597 --> 30:08.505
- You have a better view.

30:08.582 --> 30:11.341
- Oh, I doubt that.
Can I offer you some hydration?

30:11.418 --> 30:13.552
- Yeah, sure.

30:22.762 --> 30:24.855
How well do you know
the Director?

30:24.931 --> 30:27.344
- Ice?
- No, thank you.

30:27.368 --> 30:29.818
I've found him
quite evasive lately, private.

30:29.895 --> 30:32.081
- Bernard, I know you've always
felt somewhat overlooked...

30:32.105 --> 30:33.583
By our Director, for example.

30:33.607 --> 30:35.084
- Do you know he sent me
to the Savage Lands?

30:35.108 --> 30:37.534
And not on holiday, but... - Yes.

30:37.611 --> 30:39.202
- Wait, you knew?

30:39.279 --> 30:40.570
- To tell you the truth,

30:40.647 --> 30:42.275
I thought it might
do you some good.

30:42.299 --> 30:44.519
Bernard, I've always
liked you, but...

30:44.543 --> 30:47.013
I know you don't mean
to be destabilizing.

30:47.037 --> 30:48.411
- Destabilizing?
Me?

30:48.489 --> 30:51.017
- But I do worry
about how this appears.

30:51.041 --> 30:52.610
You raising these questions now,

30:52.634 --> 30:54.103
given your personal feelings
about the Director.

30:54.127 --> 30:55.552
- You're not listening.

30:55.629 --> 30:57.732
- And I know that you lost
the Savage today.

30:57.756 --> 30:58.816
- That...
- Embarrassing.

30:58.840 --> 30:59.801
- That has nothing to do
with this.

30:59.825 --> 31:01.441
- So you see my concern.

31:03.970 --> 31:05.698
Bernard, if I wasn't
hard on you,

31:05.722 --> 31:08.365
I wouldn't be doing my job.

31:22.030 --> 31:25.040
- Is that the Savage?

31:25.116 --> 31:26.458
- Yeah.

32:33.059 --> 32:35.944
- Get away from me!

32:36.021 --> 32:38.789
What are you doing?

32:38.865 --> 32:42.042
Stop it!
Stop it!

32:42.119 --> 32:44.244
Get away from me!

32:44.320 --> 32:46.858
Stop!
Get the fuck away from me!

32:54.339 --> 32:56.910
<i>Get away from me!</i>

32:56.934 --> 32:59.801
- Are you seeing this?
- Yes.

32:59.878 --> 33:02.137
- Over 100 feeds and counting.

33:03.757 --> 33:05.765
I do believe we've found
your Savage.

33:05.842 --> 33:09.269
<i>- Stop it!
Get the fuck away from me!</i>

33:09.345 --> 33:10.548
- He needs help.
Why aren't they helping him?

33:10.572 --> 33:11.980
<i>- Get the fuck away from me!</i>

33:12.057 --> 33:13.365
- Oh, my.

33:13.442 --> 33:14.744
<i>- What is this?
Stop it!</i>

33:16.269 --> 33:18.247
- Where are you going?
- H-he needs me.

33:18.271 --> 33:20.791
- Sit down, it's under control.
There are counselors en route.

33:20.815 --> 33:22.151
- I have to go.

33:22.175 --> 33:23.377
- Bernard, I'm concerned
about your behavior.

33:23.401 --> 33:25.087
- Absolutely, so am I.
Thank you.

